casebody.data:
MORRIS NEWELL ET AL., PARTNERS, ETC., RESPONDENTS, v. MAX KLIPPER ET AL., APPELLANTS. Submitted October 12, 1928 Decided April 11, 1929.

Before G-ummere, Chief Justice, and Justice Parker.

Eor the appellants, Julius J. Seiden. Eor the respondents, Isaac Gross. Per Curiam.

This is similar in all respects except the names of the plaintiffs, to the case of Schultz & Son v. Klipper, No. 63 of the present term. Eor the reasons given in the per curiam in that case, the judgment brought up in this case will be affirmed.
